A day before  what would have been her son’s 30th birthday,  a mother broke down in tears as she looked at a photograph of the young man, shot dead during a high-speed car chase  through the streets of Gqeberha after  the brazen robbery of a cash-in-transit van. Testifying on behalf of the state in the high court in Gqeberha on Wednesday, Noengland Boletyeni, 62, of Mqanduli said  the last time she saw her son Malibongwe alive had been on May 1 2018. Nine days later, she found out  he was dead.  For more on this article, please visit HeraldLIVE.